description:
&lt;p&gt;This post is for a 10 PA Locum Consultant Physician in Rheumatology comprising 8 DCC and 2 SPA sessions per week, for a fixed 6 month term. The appointee will provide a specialist rheumatological service in conjunction with eight other Rheumatology Consultants based across both the Winchester and Basingstoke sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide support primarily for our outpatient service but will also be involved with inpatient care as well, which is an integral part of the whole rheumatology service. This post will provide support for our Rheumatology outpatient service but also help us to achieve our 5 year goal of excellent care in Rheumatology including our biologics, CTD and fracture liaison services. Setting up an Ankylosing Spondylitis service, Rheumatology transition to adulthood and Fracture Liaison services are particular areas in development at the present time. Those accredited in both General Internal Medicine and Rheumatology are welcome to apply as this post, which has the option of including General Medicine. Candidates wishing to work part-time are also encouraged to apply. Candidates with an interest in a Specialist Area that compliments those of the existing team members are especially welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
